<h2 id="when-to-use-a-heading">When to use a heading</h2>

<p>Headings should be written in sentence case and follow correct semantic structure, for example h1 before h2.</p>

<p>Page heading is styled as h1 and should only be used to display the title of the page. Every page should have a unique page heading but it shouldnâ€™t appear more than once on a page.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Page heading is used at the top of each page.</li>
  <li>Content heading is used for each new and unlreated piece of content within a page.</li>
  <li>Section heading is used for each section within content on a page.</li>
  <li>Sub-section-heading is used for those occasional cases of additional breaking down within a section is required or additionally certain preview sections.</li>
</ul>
